The paper discusses the use of natural language processing and machine learning techniques to generate hypotheses from scientific literature. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of topic modeling, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The use of knowledge networks and the analysis of corpus size and document length are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL).
